ters a leading-edge strip over scroll-synced axis chrome"},"1008":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#internal-component","content":"Internal Component"},"1009":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#props","content":"Props"},"1010":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#examples","content":"Examples"},"1011":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#basic","content":"Basic"},"1012":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#internal-component","content":"This component is **internal-only** and not exported from the package. It is designed for use within chart components."},"1013":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#props","content":"The `TooltipDismissStrip` component accepts the following props:"},"1014":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#basic","content":"Tooltip provider, relative container, optional controls to open the visx tooltip and the dismiss strip on the leading edge."},"1015":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"page","content":"useNormalizedSeries","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series"},"1016":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","content":"A hook that guarantees every series config has a stable, unique id by filling in missing ones with a component-scoped prefix from useId."},"1017":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"For use with chart components (not exported)"},"1018":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#examples","content":"Examples"},"1019":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#mixed-ids","content":"Mixed ids"},"1020":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"Returns your series list with an `id` guaranteed on every item. Ids you provided are kept as-is; missing ones are filled in for you, stay stable across renders, and won't collide when multiple charts share the page."},"1021":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#mixed-ids","content":"The first item provides an explicit `id` and is preserved as-is; the remaining two have no `id` and are filled with stable generated ones (`<prefix>-1`, `<prefix>-2`)."},"1022":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"page","content":"useScrollableXYChart","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart"},"1023":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","content":"A hook for scrollable visx XY charts that measures the rendered axes and returns margins, content-sized width and height, scroll offsets, and a vertical-labels flag, so the chart sizes itself to whatever it actually contains."},"1024":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"For use with chart components (not exported)"},"1025":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#examples","content":"Examples"},"1026":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#auto-layout","content":"Auto layout"},"1027":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"**Inputs.** Wire `parentRef` to the scroll container and `xAxisRef` / `yAxisRef` to the axis groups. Optionally pass `xLabelsOrientation` (`'auto'` | `'horizontal'` | `'vertical'`, default `'auto'`) to force the category-label layout; `'auto'` rotates labels vertical when the visible width can't fit the horizontal-tick footprint plus the Y-axis width."},"1028":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"**Outputs.** The hook returns `margin`, `chartWidth`, `chartHeight`, `xLabelsVertical`, `scrollLeft` / `scrollTop`, and `yAxisRect` for the chart to consume. Width and height are sized to whichever is larger — the visible slot or the room the rendered labels need — so the chart grows past the viewport and the parent scrolls when labels demand more space."},"1029":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"**Behavior.** Measurement runs through `useParentSize`, a `MutationObserver`, and a `ResizeObserver` on the wired nodes. All axis measurements are batched in one `requestAnimationFrame` and bail out when the result hasn't changed, so a burst of observer fires costs at most one reflow and one render per frame."},"1030":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#auto-layout","content":"Hook wired to a scrolling parent; scroll or resize to watch the returned values update."},"1031":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"page","content":"Box","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Layout"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box"},"1032":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-0","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"Polymorphic layout component providing consistent spacing, elevation, rounding, and self-alignment"},"1033":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-1","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#installation","content":"Installation"},"1034":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-2","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#props","content":"Props"},"1035":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-3","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"Scale Sizes"},"1036":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-4","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#examples","content":"Examples"},"1037":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-5","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#padding","content":"Padding"},"1038":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-6","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#elevation","content":"Elevation"},"1039":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-7","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rounding","content":"Rounding"},"1040":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-8","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"Polymorphic `as` Prop"},"1041":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-9","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#alignment","content":"Alignment"},"1042":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-10","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rtl-support","content":"RTL Support"},"1043":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-11","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#design-tokens","content":"Design Tokens"},"1044":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-12","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"Box is a polymorphic layout component that renders as any HTML element or custom component via the `as` prop. It provides consistent spacing, elevation, rounding, and self-alignment within flex or grid containers."},"1045":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-13","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"**Important**: Since `Flex` and `Grid` extend `Box`, prefer them for layouts. Use `Box` only when you need a non-flex, non-grid container."},"1046":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-14","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#props","content":"The `Box` component accepts the following props:"},"1047":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-15","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"The spacing props use semantic t-shirt sizes for padding, gap, and other spacing properties:"},"1048":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-16","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`xs` - Extra small spacing"},"1049":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-17","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`sm` - Small spacing"},"1050":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-18","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`md` - Medium spacing"},"1051":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-19","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`lg` - Large spacing"},"1052":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-20","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`xl` - Extra large spacing"},"1053":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-21","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`2xl` - 2x extra large spacing"},"1054":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-22","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"Custom CSS values are also supported for edge cases."},"1055":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-23","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#padding","content":"The padding props support t-shirt sizes and CSS logical properties for RTL support."},"1056":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-24","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#elevation","content":"The elevation prop adds visual depth using box-shadow."},"1057":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-25","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rounding","content":"The rounding prop sets border-radius. Use `full` for fully rounded corners."},"1058":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-26","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"Box is fully polymorphic - the `as` prop allows rendering as any HTML element or custom component while preserving type-safe props."},"1059":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-27","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**HTML Elements:** When using `as=\"button\"`, TypeScript enforces button-specific props like `type`, `disabled`, and `onClick`."},"1060":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-28","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Custom Components:** When using `as={MyComponent}`, Box accepts that component's props. If there's a prop name conflict, Box's props take priority."},"1061":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-29","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Typed Refs:** Refs are correctly typed based on the `as` value - `useRef<HTMLButtonElement>` works with `as=\"button\"`."},"1062":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-30","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#alignment","content":"Self-alignment props allow Box to position itself within flex or grid containers."},"1063":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-31","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rtl-support","content":"Box uses CSS logical properties (`padding-inline-start`, `padding-block-end`, etc.) which automatically adapt to RTL layouts. No additional configuration is needed."},"1064":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-32","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#design-tokens","content":"All spacing, elevation, and rounding values are derived from the theme. If no theme is provided, default values are used. This ensures consistency across the design system."},"1065":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","type":"page","content":"Flex","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Layout"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/flex"},"1066":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex-0","page_id":"