mp to first/last item"],[564,"**Home/End**: Jump to first/last option"],[803,"**Horizontal charts**: Vertical scrolling when many categories exceed container height"],[835,"**Horizontal Multi-Series**: Grouped horizontal bars"],[792,"**Horizontal scrolling**: When data points exceed available width, the chart becomes horizontally scrollable"],[834,"**Horizontal Single Series**: Horizontal orientation"],[1059,"**HTML Elements:** When using `as=\"button\"`, TypeScript enforces button-specific props like `type`, `disabled`, and `onClick`."],[1045,"**Important**: Since `Flex` and `Grid` extend `Box`, prefer them for layouts. Use `Box` only when you need a non-flex, non-grid container."],[260,"**Important**: When you supply a `className`, you make a commitment to take over all styling of the component as it will remove the standard class names. Use data attributes for targeted styling instead."],[300,"**Initial Flash**: Brief moment where icons appear/disappear during sprite injection"],[1027,"**Inputs.** Wire `parentRef` to the scroll container and `xAxisRef` / `yAxisRef` to the axis groups. Optionally pass `xLabelsOrientation` (`'auto'` | `'horizontal'` | `'vertical'`, default `'auto'`) to force the category-label layout; `'auto'` rotates labels vertical when the visible width can't fit the horizontal-tick footprint plus the Y-axis width."],[709,"**Interactive tooltips**: Hover to see exact values, with smart positioning and scroll-awareness"],[158,"**isInvalid**: Shows error state styling"],[157,"**isRequired**: Marks the group as required with visual indicator"],[795,"**Keyboard navigation**: Bar groups are keyboard accessible with `tabIndex={0}` and `role=\"group\"`"],[601,"**Label, description, error**: Optional label, helper text, and error message with proper accessibility"],[84,"**Label, description, error**: Optional Label, helper Text, and FieldError with proper accessibility association"],[92,"**Label** (optional) — Rendered when `label` is provided. Shows a 